1
00:00:01,751 --> 00:00:03,712
<i>Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.</i>

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>People who have used these drugs</i>

3
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:10,635
<i>are now estimated</i>
<i>to total two million in Japan.</i>

4
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:14,347
<i>The number of people arrested</i>
<i>for drug-related offenses</i>

5
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:17,142
<i>is as many as 14,000 yearly.</i>

6
00:00:18,893 --> 00:00:20,437
The college student from before.

7
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:23,606
Another case of addiction,
like it always goes?

8
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:25,150
<i>Remember it now?</i>

9
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,234
Why?

10
00:00:26,317 --> 00:00:29,446
We used some drugs
and had a lot of fun together.

11
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:33,033
A woman with symptoms of drug addiction
was brought in this morning.

12
00:00:33,616 --> 00:00:35,952
<i>The symptoms point to cocaine addiction.</i>

13
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:37,287
No way.

14
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:39,622
Why!

15
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,291
Why are you crying?

16
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:45,044
Isn't she just a stranger?

17
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:47,172
It's just a drug addict who died.

18
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,758
Ouch!

19
00:00:49,841 --> 00:00:52,343
Are we going to let
scum like him roam free?

20
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:56,264
I'm with you. We have to keep
gathering evidence in secret for now.

21
00:00:57,015 --> 00:00:58,099
<i>A GPS tracker?</i>

22
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,685
<i>She's at her home right now.</i>

23
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:02,103
<i>If we keep track of her,</i>

24
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:05,023
we'll uncover Kaga's
true colors soon enough.

25
00:01:05,106 --> 00:01:07,609
<i>I met with that shitty Kurosaki</i>
<i>from the NCD just now.</i>

26
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:09,402
I have some info.

27
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:10,695
<i>Do you want it?</i>

28
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:13,031
I didn't expect a call
from you this quick.

29
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:15,200
Quite useful, aren't you?

30
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:19,370
Aoi?

31
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:24,918
Aoi.

32
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:33,259
Wakey-wakey.

33
00:01:39,307 --> 00:01:41,059
How do you feel?

34
00:01:48,399 --> 00:01:49,400
Morning.

35
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:53,363
Remember anything?

36
00:01:58,159 --> 00:01:59,661
Or not yet?

37
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:39,492
Hello?

38
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:41,161
Aoi left her apartment.

39
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,038
Okay. Tail her and make contact.

40
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:45,248
What?

41
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:49,919
Use any means to figure out
where Kaga gets his cocaine from.

42
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:54,007
We'll use that information
to crush the whole operation.

43
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:56,175
Come on, you're asking a lot here.

44
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:58,887
Weren't you an actor before?

45
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:01,598
Figure it out.

46
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:04,017
How is that relevant?
Don't you have a plan?

47
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:05,727
Don't be a baby.

48
00:03:05,810 --> 00:03:09,480
A good spy needs to think for themselves
without being too reliant on others.

49
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:10,732
Figure it out.

50
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:16,779
You've got to be kidding me.

51
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,198
I don't want to be a good spy.

52
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:44,515
You okay?

53
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:47,727
Sorry.

54
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:49,938
I'm fine.

55
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:53,524
You don't look fine to me.

56
00:03:58,863 --> 00:04:00,281
Do you have a fever?

57
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:02,533
You're sweating a ton.

58
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:10,601
Here.

59
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:12,145
Thank you.

60
00:05:12,228 --> 00:05:14,731
Had me worried with the way you collapsed.

61
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:19,527
Maybe I ate something weird.

62
00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:28,244
Wait.

63
00:05:32,915 --> 00:05:37,086
Did you ever star in a movie
called <i>School King</i>?

64
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:38,379
Yeah.

65
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:41,758
My mother was an extra in it
ten years ago,

66
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:44,218
and I had a small part in it too.

67
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:46,095
Wow, really?

68
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:48,681
Sorry, you probably don't remember me.

69
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:50,308
No, I remember you.

70
00:05:50,391 --> 00:05:51,559
Wait, really?

71
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:53,269
Of course, I do.

72
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:56,481
How you've grown.

73
00:05:57,523 --> 00:06:02,111
Oh, but I don't think
my height has changed all that much.

74
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:05,031
Well, I mean, you've gotten mature.

75
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:08,659
Women get this different aura
about them as time goes by.

76
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:13,206
It's fine.

77
00:06:13,706 --> 00:06:17,752
Of course, you wouldn't remember
an extra from ten years ago.

78
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:19,962
Sorry.

79
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:24,509
Wait, but I remember back then,

80
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:28,888
filming was going a bit long,
and I ended up crying.

81
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:33,643
You kept me company the whole break.

82
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:38,815
Oh, now, I actually remember you.

83
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:43,486
You were crying a ton, right?
You had snot all over your face.

84
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:47,156
I got snot on my costume.
It was such a mess.

85
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,324
Sorry.

86
00:06:48,407 --> 00:06:51,160
No, I'm sorry
for not remembering you sooner.

87
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:54,789
But wow, what a coincidence.

88
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:03,714
That stalker woman committed suicide.

89
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:06,968
The police and NCD are taking action.

90
00:07:07,051 --> 00:07:09,428
She's a pain in the ass, even in death.

91
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:10,680
Damn it.

92
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:13,182
You sure she didn't leave a will?

93
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:18,312
The people I asked to handle the cleanup
said they found nothing in her room.

94
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:20,565
It's going to be fine.

95
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:22,358
Things are far from fine!

96
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:27,196
Lay low for a while, okay?

97
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,073
Right.

98
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:30,408
But you know,

99
00:07:31,409 --> 00:07:36,956
seeing the face of someone drooling
in bliss from the cocaine I fed them…

100
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:44,005
It gets me so turned on.

101
00:07:54,932 --> 00:07:56,267
It doesn't sound

102
00:07:57,351 --> 00:08:00,438
like you just happened
to eat something bad.

103
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:08,488
Some time ago,
I was in a movie that focused on drugs.

104
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:12,366
Your symptoms sound very familiar.

105
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:16,329
Could it be that…

106
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:22,210
I might be able to help you out.

107
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:23,794
Can you tell me more?

108
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:33,179
I can't.

109
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:35,848
Why?

110
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:40,102
Because,

111
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:43,231
if I do…

112
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:47,360
It would suck if this got
shared publicly, wouldn't it?

113
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:54,075
Damn it, this is getting annoying.

114
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:55,743
What?

115
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:57,537
There's a rumor

116
00:08:57,620 --> 00:09:02,416
that a certain celebrity forcefully feeds
cocaine to women and assaults them.

117
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:06,796
So hearing your story got me concerned.

118
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,174
And that celebrity is?

119
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:15,304
Hibiki Kaga.

120
00:09:24,021 --> 00:09:25,356
Did that ring a bell?

121
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:28,234
Does he have dirt on you?

122
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:35,491
If you don't do anything,
you'll be an addict in a month's time.

123
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,119
Are you okay with that?

124
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:44,375
I've seen many people
whose lives were ruined by drugs.

125
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:47,753
I don't want you to turn out the same.

126
00:09:50,881 --> 00:09:52,508
I can figure something out.

127
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:56,596
I just need you to tell me
if Kaga gets in touch with you.

128
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:04,562
There's no going back
once you get addicted.

129
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:07,565
Are you okay with hurting
those dear to you

130
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:10,151
and losing everything?

131
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:21,037
Please…

132
00:10:23,247 --> 00:10:24,665
help me.

133
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:03,371
What is it?

134
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:07,750
<i>Aoi was fed cocaine by Kaga.</i>

135
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:10,586
You sure?

136
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:13,798
<i>Kaga told her to come</i>
<i>to a club in Roppongi tonight.</i>

137
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:16,467
Good job.

138
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:47,373
<i>That said, you really think</i>
<i>Kaga would go to a club?</i>

139
00:11:47,456 --> 00:11:50,418
<i>A woman he got addicted</i>
<i>to cocaine took her life.</i>

140
00:11:51,043 --> 00:11:55,464
Word must have gotten out
that you and the police are on the case.

141
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:58,551
The scary thing about drugs
is that you can't stop.

142
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:03,222
What about Aoi?

143
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,392
Like I would let her come.

144
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:10,229
I told her to make up
an excuse and turn Kaga down.

145
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:14,567
I'll help her somehow.

146
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:15,985
You of all people?

147
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,611
Why not me?

148
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,655
Get off my back.

149
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:29,123
- Oh, there he is.
- We were waiting for you, Mr. Kaga.

150
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,126
- Heya.
- Let's go in.

151
00:12:32,209 --> 00:12:34,086
He really did come.

152
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:37,548
I'm in Roppongi for the Kaga case.
Be ready to mobilize.

153
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:44,388
Club A2. That's where the rapper Igarashi
died by overdose after stabbing a waiter.

154
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:46,640
That was here?

155
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:49,226
They were closed for a while
after that incident,

156
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:51,353
but they're throwing
a regulars-only party today,

157
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:54,857
and dealing cocaine to guests
in the VIP room through waiters.

158
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:56,609
Gotcha.

159
00:12:56,692 --> 00:12:58,611
That's where you come in.

160
00:12:58,694 --> 00:13:00,529
- What?
- Sneak in.

161
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:01,906
What?

162
00:13:02,406 --> 00:13:03,657
Come on, man.

163
00:13:03,741 --> 00:13:07,244
If you already know that much,
just go in there with the whole NCD.

164
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:11,123
If we go now, we'll only catch
the waiters at best.

165
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:14,543
You're the key for us to get Kaga.

166
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:19,048
Yeah, but the party
is only open to their regulars.

167
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:20,883
I'm not a regular here.

168
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:24,553
You think they'll just let me
into such a crazy party that easily?

169
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:28,766
I didn't say to go in as a guest.

170
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:34,438
What's this?

171
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:37,274
<i>Bite-sized Love</i>
<i>at a Family Restaurant</i>, was it?

172
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:39,944
You played a waiter in it.

173
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:43,822
Did you check all the dramas I was in?

174
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:46,158
Not all of them. Just three.

175
00:13:47,034 --> 00:13:49,370
This is a keycard for club personnel.

176
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:51,956
Why do you have this?

177
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:55,376
I picked it up at the hospital
from the waiter who got stabbed.

178
00:13:58,629 --> 00:13:59,630
Do I get any--

179
00:13:59,713 --> 00:14:01,298
- I'll arrest you.
- Let me finish!

180
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:15,437
<i>Find Kaga.</i>

181
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:17,690
I'm on it.

182
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:19,567
So annoying.

183
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:22,111
<i>I can still hear you.</i>

184
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:30,619
Found him.

185
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:36,041
Go ahead.

186
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:43,883
Excuse me.

187
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:50,472
Here you are. Please come in.

188
00:15:02,234 --> 00:15:03,819
He went into the VIP room.

189
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:07,907
<i>If Kaga does cocaine, record evidence</i>
<i>with your phone and contact me.</i>

190
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:10,659
<i>That will be my cue</i>
<i>to enter and arrest him.</i>

191
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:13,287
Okay, I'll let you know
if anything happens.

192
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:18,584
Gotta find a way into the VIP room first.

193
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:29,887
Hello, can you hear me?

194
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:30,930
<i>Yeah.</i>

195
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:33,641
Contact me the moment Kaga does cocaine.

196
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:34,975
<i>Got it.</i>

197
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:36,685
I will not tolerate failure.

198
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:38,520
Gotcha.

199
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:43,150
Just watch, NCD asshat.

200
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:45,653
I'll get him first.

201
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:00,376
<i>Hey.</i>

202
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:02,127
Still no updates?

203
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:04,505
<i>Can you not put more pressure on me?</i>

204
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:09,885
I'll get back to you.

205
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:14,014
Hello, sir.

206
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:15,099
Who're you?

207
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:17,977
Can I handle the VIP room today?

208
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:20,938
What? No one told me about this.

209
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:35,411
So heavy!

210
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:36,870
Damn it.

211
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:48,507
Perfect.

212
00:16:51,927 --> 00:16:53,345
Excuse me.

213
00:16:57,307 --> 00:16:58,642
Who are you?

214
00:16:59,184 --> 00:17:04,106
My colleague fell ill and had to leave,
so I will be filling in as his substitute.

215
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:06,483
Fine.

216
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:09,862
Mr. Kaga.

217
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:14,783
I have some good stuff for you.

218
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:17,536
Huh?

219
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:20,789
It's ultra-fine stuff from Syria.

220
00:17:21,498 --> 00:17:25,836
My colleague said you could have it
on the house, since you're a patron.

221
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:35,971
My grandma always told me
not to accept gifts from strangers.

222
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:40,392
I'm not gonna trust a guy I just met.

223
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:43,854
Care to try it?

224
00:17:44,563 --> 00:17:45,939
Just a taste.

225
00:17:53,363 --> 00:17:54,823
If you get high on it,

226
00:17:56,658 --> 00:17:59,244
I'll buy enough for everyone here.

227
00:17:59,328 --> 00:18:00,329
What?

228
00:18:00,954 --> 00:18:03,540
Oh, but I'm not in the mood today.

229
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:04,666
Come on.

230
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:09,880
- Ow.
- Get to it.

231
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:13,008
But…

232
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:16,553
You really a dealer?

233
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:22,226
I understand.

234
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:25,562
I'll do it.

235
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:40,994
Goddamn it!

236
00:18:43,831 --> 00:18:46,125
You're a fun guy, aren't you?

237
00:18:47,084 --> 00:18:48,418
Care to join me,

238
00:18:49,586 --> 00:18:50,754
Mr. Kaga?

239
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:54,842
If this stuff really does the job,

240
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:57,678
I'll buy from you from now on.

241
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:19,825
Holy crap!

242
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:24,997
So good.

243
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:30,878
You guys try it too.

244
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:36,133
This rocks!

245
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:52,357
I did it, Katsuragi.

246
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:54,568
Kaga just did cocaine.

247
00:19:55,194 --> 00:19:56,987
I left to avoid any trouble.

248
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:58,947
Get back to Kaga right now.

249
00:19:59,823 --> 00:20:02,534
What? Screw that.

250
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:05,287
I just inhaled a full dose
of Loxoprofen Sodium.

251
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:07,206
<i>Of course, I'm gonna scram.</i>

252
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:09,583
Loxoprofen Sodium.

253
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:11,627
You really a dealer?

254
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:13,253
I understand.

255
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:14,504
I'll do it.

256
00:20:20,427 --> 00:20:21,929
<i>I kept my end of the deal</i>

257
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:24,056
and contacted you
as soon as Kaga did drugs.

258
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:26,266
Just go arrest him or whatever.

259
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:28,227
Listen. To arrest someone for drugs,

260
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:31,396
the police must either have evidence
or catch them in the act.

261
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,775
However, Kaga is inside a building
owned by an acquaintance.

262
00:20:34,858 --> 00:20:37,527
I have no evidence
that Kaga actually did drugs.

263
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:40,864
Without evidence, the courts
won't issue a search warrant,

264
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:43,951
so I can't do a search,
meaning I can't catch him in the act.

265
00:20:44,034 --> 00:20:47,704
Meaning you need to get your ass
back to the VIP room right now!

266
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:49,498
I told you,

267
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:53,335
he's doing cocaine in there right now!
Just go catch him in the act!

268
00:20:54,586 --> 00:20:55,921
And how do I know that?

269
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:58,382
What?

270
00:20:59,091 --> 00:21:01,677
No, seriously, you lost me there.

271
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:05,097
Because I saw it and reported it to you.
That's evidence!

272
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:07,599
<i>Isn't that how sting operations work?</i>

273
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:08,892
Sting operations?

274
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:10,143
Yeah.

275
00:21:10,227 --> 00:21:12,980
The police aren't allowed
to carry out sting operations.

276
00:21:13,063 --> 00:21:16,441
You're ultimately only moving
under my personal instructions.

277
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,026
<i>What?</i>

278
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:19,569
Let's say I arrest Kaga.

279
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:21,071
Unless you're in there with him,

280
00:21:21,154 --> 00:21:23,949
how am I gonna explain
how I knew what he was doing in there?

281
00:21:24,616 --> 00:21:27,828
I don't really get it,
and your dialect is leaking.

282
00:21:27,911 --> 00:21:29,496
This is such a huge pain!

283
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:33,625
Plus, Kaga consumed cocaine
after you offered it to him, right?

284
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:35,419
Yeah, I put myself at risk to do it.

285
00:21:36,211 --> 00:21:40,173
I told you to coax him
into obtaining drugs of his own accord!

286
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:42,759
Let's say this goes to court.

287
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:46,221
What if they argue that he was entrapped
into doing cocaine

288
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:48,849
<i>by some lackey</i>
<i>that the police put up to it?</i>

289
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:49,933
What about it?

290
00:21:50,017 --> 00:21:52,728
<i>If the court rules it</i>
<i>an illegal investigation,</i>

291
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:53,812
<i>Kaga will walk free.</i>

292
00:21:53,895 --> 00:21:57,149
And if the police are found guilty
of entrapment,

293
00:21:57,232 --> 00:21:58,984
it will reflect badly on me.

294
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:00,319
If it comes to that,

295
00:22:00,402 --> 00:22:02,738
<i>how do you plan to make up for it?</i>

296
00:22:04,364 --> 00:22:06,908
So you're only concerned about yourself?

297
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:09,119
Of course, I am. Now, get back in there!

298
00:22:09,202 --> 00:22:10,954
Go in and scream somewhere randomly

299
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:13,248
that Kaga was about
to make you do cocaine.

300
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:16,168
Then I'll take him in
as I go in to investigate.

301
00:22:16,251 --> 00:22:20,881
We can add on charges for possession
and use of cocaine after the fact.

302
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:25,010
As long as the rule
of law exists in Japan,

303
00:22:25,093 --> 00:22:28,138
we have to prioritize
optics above all else!

304
00:22:28,221 --> 00:22:31,141
Screw that! You're just trying
to cover your own ass!

305
00:22:31,224 --> 00:22:32,350
What?

306
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:35,479
Remember your place, damn S.

307
00:22:35,562 --> 00:22:37,314
Shut up! I don't care!

308
00:22:40,317 --> 00:22:42,527
Damn jackass piece of shit!

309
00:22:46,364 --> 00:22:47,574
Shit.

310
00:22:48,075 --> 00:22:48,992
Hey.

311
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:49,993
You scared me.

312
00:22:50,077 --> 00:22:52,204
Why weren't you responding?

313
00:22:52,954 --> 00:22:56,500
Well, I got Kaga to do cocaine.

314
00:22:58,043 --> 00:23:00,087
But that's not good enough, right?

315
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,589
You did well.

316
00:23:03,465 --> 00:23:04,382
What?

317
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:08,678
I'll go inside the club now
and arrest Kaga for possession of cocaine.

318
00:23:08,762 --> 00:23:11,640
But I thought you weren't allowed
to do sting operations.

319
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:14,643
Yeah, it's not allowed.

320
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:18,063
For those fools in the police.

321
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:23,568
We're allowed the ultimate weapon
that the police can't use.

322
00:23:23,652 --> 00:23:25,612
Sting operations.

323
00:23:25,695 --> 00:23:27,948
That's the NCD's prerogative.

324
00:23:28,031 --> 00:23:29,199
Let's go.

325
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:41,336
Hurry up and jump.

326
00:23:41,419 --> 00:23:42,754
MAD DOG KUROSAKI RUNS WILD

327
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:44,506
- I didn't do anything!
- Screw you!

328
00:23:44,589 --> 00:23:47,092
<i>Even if it was against their will,</i>

329
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:50,262
<i>once consumed, one's body</i>
<i>will never forget the taste of drugs.</i>

330
00:23:50,345 --> 00:23:54,432
I will never consider you a human being.

331
00:23:54,975 --> 00:24:00,897
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS,
GROUPS, OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

332
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:01,940
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan
